WEBVTT

1
00:00:04.130 --> 00:00:08.010
I'm clockin' out early, hey, hey, hey.

2
00:00:12.450 --> 00:00:15.010
Next customer, please step this way.

3
00:00:15.010 --> 00:00:17.140
Oh... okay.

4
00:00:29.450 --> 00:00:31.190
That'll be 1,040 yen.

5
00:00:31.190 --> 00:00:32.780
Okay.

6
00:00:33.160 --> 00:00:35.160
Here's your change and receipt.

7
00:00:35.770 --> 00:00:38.410
You're close to getting 
your loyalty reward!

8
00:00:38.710 --> 00:00:39.410
Okay...

9
00:00:39.680 --> 00:00:42.420
We'll have a 50% discount coupon 
on mochi chips tomorrow.

10
00:00:42.950 --> 00:00:44.370
Thanks.

11
00:00:52.830 --> 00:00:55.370
I'll take over, Yamada-chan.

12
00:00:55.370 --> 00:00:56.480
Something's wrong.

13
00:00:56.480 --> 00:00:57.430
What?

14
00:00:57.430 --> 00:01:00.080
Wow, I have so many points now.

15
00:01:00.080 --> 00:01:01.690
Thank you very much!

16
00:01:02.170 --> 00:01:05.680
My customer service 
didn't prove effective.

17
00:01:05.680 --> 00:01:06.830
On what?

18
00:01:11.650 --> 00:01:14.570
I want to smoke so bad.

19
00:02:58.090 --> 00:03:00.170
Tayama-san...

20
00:03:03.180 --> 00:03:06.640
I can't smoke here without her. 
It's not that easy.

21
00:03:08.100 --> 00:03:10.190
Heya, it's me, your easy girl.

22
00:03:12.690 --> 00:03:13.880
Tayama-san?!

23
00:03:14.460 --> 00:03:16.150
Wassup?

24
00:03:16.690 --> 00:03:19.040
Oh, did you just get off?

25
00:03:19.040 --> 00:03:19.960
Yep.

26
00:03:19.960 --> 00:03:21.160
Good work.

27
00:03:21.740 --> 00:03:25.140
Anyway, you want to smoke, right? 
Isn't that why you're here?

28
00:03:25.140 --> 00:03:26.660
Get in.

29
00:03:37.120 --> 00:03:38.820
That was one big sigh.

30
00:03:39.440 --> 00:03:41.880
Something got you down, Sasaki-san?

31
00:03:41.880 --> 00:03:43.300
Uh, well...

32
00:03:43.720 --> 00:03:45.010
I guess.

33
00:03:49.320 --> 00:03:51.560
Yamada-san was bothered by it.

34
00:03:51.560 --> 00:03:55.650
What? Did I act 
inappropriately back there?

35
00:03:55.650 --> 00:03:56.820
Not what I meant.

36
00:03:57.410 --> 00:04:00.820
She was worried about you 
because you were down in the dumps.

37
00:04:03.940 --> 00:04:08.660
She's such a considerate, 
thoughtful person.

38
00:04:09.080 --> 00:04:11.090
Thank you, too, Tayama-san.

39
00:04:11.090 --> 00:04:13.280
Hey, I'm just the messenger.

40
00:04:13.280 --> 00:04:17.960
What? But you came here 
just to tell me that, didn't you?

41
00:04:19.210 --> 00:04:24.590
Your hair's down, so I thought maybe 
you rushed here to talk to me.

42
00:04:26.400 --> 00:04:30.690
Hey, Tayama-san! You know you 
shouldn't blow smoke in someone's face!

43
00:04:35.370 --> 00:04:38.500
I couldn't be bothered 
doing my hair. That's all.

44
00:04:39.380 --> 00:04:41.250
And I passed on the message because...

45
00:04:44.250 --> 00:04:46.100
I'm not telling you.

46
00:04:46.590 --> 00:04:49.690
You can blame yourself 
for getting cheeky tonight.

47
00:04:52.290 --> 00:04:54.100
Cheeky? What?

48
00:04:54.620 --> 00:04:56.600
H-How do you mean?

49
00:04:56.600 --> 00:04:58.560
Too cheeky for such a dense guy.

50
00:04:58.560 --> 00:05:00.880
Excuse me? I am not dense.

51
00:05:06.130 --> 00:05:08.460
Am I really that dense?

52
00:05:08.460 --> 00:05:09.640
What's the matter?

53
00:05:10.250 --> 00:05:12.490
Tayama-san, uh...

54
00:05:13.370 --> 00:05:17.480
Could I get your unbiased thoughts 
on something? I'd appreciate it.

55
00:05:17.480 --> 00:05:18.620
What is it?

56
00:05:20.220 --> 00:05:21.820
Am I a scary guy?

57
00:05:23.930 --> 00:05:25.640
Are you okay?

58
00:05:25.640 --> 00:05:28.290
Where'd that hilarious question come from?

59
00:05:28.290 --> 00:05:29.340
"Hilarious"?

60
00:05:30.120 --> 00:05:31.330
Well, you see...

61
00:05:35.130 --> 00:05:39.670
I made a fresh-out-of-college 
hire cry today.

62
00:05:39.670 --> 00:05:44.730
What, Sasaki-san, are you the yelly 
type at work? That's so funny.

63
00:05:44.730 --> 00:05:47.140
Hey! Now look here, you... You...!

64
00:05:47.140 --> 00:05:49.050
No! Absolutely not!

65
00:05:49.990 --> 00:05:52.180
She made a really trivial mistake,

66
00:05:52.180 --> 00:05:54.900
so I tried to cheer her up,

67
00:05:54.900 --> 00:05:57.630
but I think she took 
what I said the opposite way.

68
00:06:25.680 --> 00:06:29.760
I'd feel so bad if she came 
to hate her job because of me.

69
00:06:36.510 --> 00:06:38.480
I don't see the problem.

70
00:06:38.480 --> 00:06:43.670
Your workplace is basically a sweatshop, 
making you work so late all the time.

71
00:06:43.670 --> 00:06:45.120
She'll probably quit either way.

72
00:06:45.120 --> 00:06:47.650
Don't say that, Tayama-san...

73
00:06:49.750 --> 00:06:53.990
Besides, if she's a fresh graduate, 
she only just joined the company, right?

74
00:06:54.830 --> 00:06:59.850
She'll eventually find out 
that you're a good person.

75
00:07:03.560 --> 00:07:06.700
Well, if she sticks around that long.

76
00:07:07.290 --> 00:07:08.860
Thanks for saying so.

77
00:07:13.320 --> 00:07:17.350
I'm sure Yamada-san would never 
find herself in this situation.

78
00:07:17.770 --> 00:07:19.440
Why bring her up there?

79
00:07:19.440 --> 00:07:26.280
I just thought, she'd never scare 
new hires to the point of tears.

80
00:07:27.710 --> 00:07:32.780
Unlike me and my intimidating 
appearance, you mean?

81
00:07:32.780 --> 00:07:34.920
That's not what I meant.

82
00:07:34.920 --> 00:07:40.850
True, she's more likely 
to be disrespected than feared.

83
00:07:40.850 --> 00:07:43.000
Disrespected?

84
00:07:45.210 --> 00:07:47.700
I really think she's incredible.

85
00:07:47.700 --> 00:07:50.270
She's bright and cheery, 
even when working at odd hours,

86
00:07:50.270 --> 00:07:53.100
and she even looks out 
for troublesome customers like me.

87
00:07:53.550 --> 00:07:57.190
I wish I could go about things 
with a smile like her.

88
00:08:02.290 --> 00:08:06.520
Supermarkets train their employees hard 
to have the perfect smile.

89
00:08:06.520 --> 00:08:10.120
Oh, really? Does that mean you, too?

90
00:08:10.120 --> 00:08:10.870
Yep.

91
00:08:11.190 --> 00:08:13.280
Your eyes have to be 
upturned and crescent.

92
00:08:13.280 --> 00:08:14.950
Lift your facial muscles,

93
00:08:15.370 --> 00:08:17.420
and show your upper teeth.

94
00:08:19.200 --> 00:08:20.240
Like so!

95
00:08:23.250 --> 00:08:26.590
T-Tamaya-san, you...

96
00:08:29.500 --> 00:08:30.300
Huh?

97
00:08:32.770 --> 00:08:33.550
Wha?

98
00:08:34.210 --> 00:08:36.350
Sorry. I'm really sorry.

99
00:08:37.060 --> 00:08:40.100
It's just, that really took me aback.

100
00:08:40.780 --> 00:08:44.180
You look great when you're acting 
all cutesy, too, Tayama-san.

101
00:08:47.610 --> 00:08:48.510
Huh?

102
00:08:49.110 --> 00:08:50.910
T... Tayama-san?

103
00:08:52.880 --> 00:08:55.600
No, I should be apologizing to you.

104
00:08:55.600 --> 00:08:58.620
Rather than just demonstrating, 
I should have instructed you directly.

105
00:08:58.620 --> 00:09:00.870
S-Sowwy, 'ayama-han!

106
00:09:00.870 --> 00:09:01.870
A you ma'?

107
00:09:01.870 --> 00:09:04.680
I din't mean anying 'y it!

108
00:09:07.380 --> 00:09:10.410
Okay. That'll do for smile practice.

109
00:09:17.410 --> 00:09:19.280
I'm sorry, okay?

110
00:09:20.710 --> 00:09:23.390
Remember that feeling and practice more.

111
00:09:23.390 --> 00:09:24.200
I...

112
00:09:24.200 --> 00:09:24.940
Got that?

113
00:09:24.940 --> 00:09:25.750
Yes, ma'am!

114
00:09:29.100 --> 00:09:33.030
I'm really sorry 
for breaking down yesterday!

115
00:09:34.420 --> 00:09:37.780
I didn't mean to cry, but...

116
00:09:38.240 --> 00:09:40.800
I was just so overwhelmed.

117
00:09:40.800 --> 00:09:42.820
Let's talk outside. 
It's too smoky in here.

118
00:09:42.820 --> 00:09:44.260
No, that's fine.

119
00:09:44.790 --> 00:09:48.880
I'm truly sorry for making you out 
to be the bad guy.

120
00:09:48.880 --> 00:09:51.880
Don't be. I should've thought 
about my phrasing, too.

121
00:09:51.880 --> 00:09:54.300
There's no need! I...

122
00:09:54.300 --> 00:09:57.900
I knew you were a good person. 
I shouldn't have misunderstood.

123
00:10:08.640 --> 00:10:11.640
It's totally normal to mess up at first. 
In fact, you're expected to.

124
00:10:11.640 --> 00:10:13.490
Don't let it get to you.

125
00:10:13.490 --> 00:10:16.350
And if you ever have any questions, 
don't hesitate to ask.

126
00:10:16.790 --> 00:10:18.260
Thank you very much.

127
00:10:21.250 --> 00:10:22.510
What a smooth operator.

128
00:10:22.510 --> 00:10:25.200
Don't ruin it!

129
00:10:30.030 --> 00:10:32.960
Next customer, please step this way.

130
00:10:37.110 --> 00:10:39.470
Here's your receipt.

131
00:10:40.380 --> 00:10:41.970
Thank you.

132
00:10:42.370 --> 00:10:44.060
Thank you! Come again!

133
00:11:01.190 --> 00:11:03.180
Don't laugh at that, Sasaki.

134
00:11:06.240 --> 00:11:08.140
You see it all the time.
